title.rendered: Antoine Walker Sued For Ganking Fiancee

content.rendered:
Reading Time: < 1 minute

Former NBA star Antoine Walker is being sued a guy for $5 million.

The charge? That ‘Toine stole his fiancee! He’s accused of putting the moves on an engaged woman a few months ago, then laughing when dumped him.

Kevin Jenkins says he actually caught his fiancee having “an intimate moment” with Walker back in October and decided he would approach the pair.

That suit and ring have likely been repossessed.

At that point, “Mr. Walker taunted and laughed at Jenkins with the intent of causing him emotional distress.” Jenkins says he became suicidal as a result.

Now, he wants Antoine to cough up that sum. Good luck with that, given Walker’s very serious financial problems. Dude blew like $100 million bucks!

Oddly enough, Walker himself was engaged to Evelyn Lozada (above) before he went broke and she glommed on to Chad Ochocino instead. Go figure.
